CatDescriptText: La Salle Beauty School, 2107 Centre Avenue, was run by Wynona Graves, Beatrice Farrish, Evelyn Farrish, Veola Moon, and Louise Farrish.  This school trained beauticians.  Signs in the windows of the building advertise it as 'La Salle Training School Beauty Culture.' The car parked in front is a Ford 1935 V-8 Deluxe Tudor sedan, c. 1935-1945.  La Salle Beauty School was started in the mid-1920s and closed in the late 1930s or early 1940s.
